Faced with European resistance, in Germany we are beginning to speculate on the three possible exits from the crisis.
The first, a strong euro, integrated by itself, Austria and Holland, among other countries, and the south would abandon the monetary zone.
The second, the recovery of the Mark, although now it seems to be science fiction, with a very favourable current of opinion, almost 50% of the population.
The third is a new concept of the euro, in line with the German proposals for greater macro-economic control, budgetary strictness, fines to countries which violate them, possible suspensions of payments of one of them and extension to the private sector of the costs of potential adjustments.
