Finally, towards the end of October, Merkel again expresses a clear position, asking for the reform of the Union's treaties to make it possible for a country's rescue and at the same time to oblige private lenders to bear a share of the cost.
This position has been interpreted as anti-European, as it has precipitated the Irish crisis and the rest.
