Seniors experienced a slight increase in unemployment, at 6.4% in metropolitan areas (+0.2 points over three months and over a year), i.e. 482,000 people aged 50 or over, and 6.6% with DOMs.
Only the 25-49-year-olds benefited from unemployment stability in the third quarter, at 8.3% in metropolitan areas (-0.1 point over three months, +0.1 point over one year) and 8.8% throughout France.
Insee no longer publishes monthly unemployment rates since 2006, after a polemic on its method of calculation.
Eurostat, the statistical agency of the European Union, on the other hand, continues to do so and announced on Tuesday a rate of 9.8% for France (including DOM) in October after 9.9% in September.
