Vengeance hackers and spies in diligence
The WikiLeaks case has a double value.
On the one hand, there is an apparent scandal, a scandal which only appears as a scandal in the face of hypocrisy which governs relations between states, citizens and the press.
On the other hand, it announces profound changes at the international level, and foreshadows a future dominated by regression.
But let's do it in order.
The first aspect of WikiLeaks is the confirmation that each file consisting of a secret service (of any nation) consists exclusively of press cuts.
