Video cassettes (analogues) had allowed cinematographers to explore a film step by step, going forward and backwards and discovering all the secrets of the installation, while now the CDs (digital) only allow to jump from chapter to chapter, i.e. by macroportions.
With the high-speed trains, we go from Rome to Milan in three hours, while on the plane, and the travel that it includes, it takes three and a half hours.
